My uncle Mr Boldbaatar lives with his wife, daughter and grand - daughter in Mongolian traditional house Ger. Since he became pensioner, he tried to find a job, but the age was the main problem. Then he bought few pigs on the money that he had, and started his subsistence Pig Framing business with 8 pigs in rented pig shelter. The shelter was not technically for pigs, so the winter 2009-2010 became the worst ever winter for him. All piglets have died (30), pigs have lost their weights, and mostly they were nearly frozen, as the winter in Mongolia is about – 40 C.
Now as the summer coming, he wishes to build a shelter for his remaining pigs, warm enough to get thru any winter and grow his pigs and coming piglets to make the business out of it. This is the time for him to prepare for the winter times and build a proper shelter for his Pig Farm.
His family is in a very need of fund to build a shelter for pigs. For this he needs to buy all necessary parts and equipments. If he won’t be able to build a shelter, the pigs are not able to survive anymore winters. He really needs to overcome this situation and make this business to go, as he doesn’t have other choices. Please help them to raise the fund of $2500 and he will be able to repay within 2 years.
Thank you.
